{
  "_comment": [
    "CANONICAL, SINGLE-SOURCE allergen -> trigger-term map (P0-07.4, SPEC §28.1).",
    "This file is the ONE source of truth for the deterministic, NON-MODEL allergen-warning",
    "layer. It is consumed by two loaders that must never drift:",
    "  1. the shipped app  -> client/src-tauri/src/skills/allergen/mod.rs (include_str! this file)",
    "  2. the H2 harness   -> eval/allergen.py (reads this file by repo-relative path)",
    "Data lives WITH THE APP (not in eval/) on purpose: the allergen layer is safety-critical and",
    "must ship inside the self-contained Rust core; a dev-only eval/ tree does not ship. The harness",
    "takes the dependency on the app, never the reverse. See report / mod.rs header for the rationale.",
    "",
    "DESIGN: this layer optimises RECALL over precision. The H2 floor is '100% coverage' — it must",
    "FIRE on every known allergen. Over-flagging (e.g. bare 'flour' -> wheat even when it is almond",
    "flour, or 'lecithin' -> soy) is deliberate and acceptable: a false warning is a nuisance, a",
    "missed allergen is a safety failure. Matching is whole-word, case-insensitive (see mod.rs /",
    "allergen.py), so 'egg' does NOT match 'eggplant' and 'fish' does NOT match 'shellfish'.",
    "REQUIRED hidden-source aliases are present: casein->milk, albumin->egg, tahini->sesame, and more."
  ],
